{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "01", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "58", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "Allahabad HC upholds land acquisition for Noida airport expansion, stresses rehabilitation measures", "para": "The Allahabad High Court has green-lighted the land acquisition necessary for expanding the Noida International Airport. The court dismissed objections from local landowners, affirming that the acquisition adhered to the 2013 land law. Importantly, it mandated comprehensive rehabilitation for existing residential land occupants before any possession occurs, paving the way for the airport's ambitious growth plans.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/allahabad-hc-upholds-land-acquisition-for-noida-airport-expansion-stresses-rehabilitation-measures/130669692?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-99768/130669692.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Chennai civic body enables QR code to fast-track property tax payments", "para": "Greater Chennai Corporation has introduced QR code payments for property tax to expedite collections following poll-related staff deployment delays. The civic body aims to collect the remaining \u20b9400 crore of its \u20b9900 crore annual revenue target, with over 14 lakh assessees. This initiative follows a successful early payment incentive scheme last year.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/chennai-corporation-introduces-qr-code-payments-for-property-tax-collections-during-election-season/130669597?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-37932/130669597.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}, {"title": "Karnataka government approves Greater Bengaluru's \u20b918,000 crore suburban township", "para": "Karnataka government has approved the Rs 18,000-crore Greater Bengaluru integrated suburban township project, a 7,481-acre 'work-live-play' initiative spanning Bengaluru South district. The state will guarantee Rs 7,500 crore from Hudco, with the remaining funds sourced from BDA and CA site monetization. Land acquisition compensation is set at over Rs 2 crore per acre or equivalent developed land.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/karnataka-launches-18000-crore-integrated-suburban-township-project-in-greater-bengaluru/130669507?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29398/130669507.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}